After all, they were living at home much longer than previous generations, earning less, and taking on much more student debt.
And 27% of millennial buyers are planning on borrowing their down payment from friends or family, with an average loan of $10,000.
But even among buyers of conventional homes, the spaces that millennials are looking at are significantly smaller than previous generations.
On the other hand, nearly half of millennial buyers would gladly sign a mortgage that came with a 6% interest rate.
Economic necessity has forced them to consider smaller homes than previous generations, in less pleasant locations, and many millennial homeowners regret their purchase.